# Django Guidelines

## Project Structure
- Follow Django's recommended project structure
- Use apps to organize related functionality
- Store settings in config/ or separate files
- Place static files in static/ directories
- Use templates/ for template files

## Model Conventions
- Follow Django's ORM patterns
- Implement proper model relationships
- Use appropriate field types and constraints
- Implement proper model validation
- Follow naming conventions for models and fields

## View Conventions
- Use class-based views when appropriate
- Keep views focused and modular
- Implement proper error handling
- Use Django's built-in view decorators
- Follow the DRY principle in views

## URL Routing
- Use URL patterns effectively
- Implement proper URL organization
- Use namespace and app_name appropriately
- Follow RESTful URL patterns when possible
- Implement proper URL security

## Templates
- Use Django's template engine
- Follow template inheritance patterns
- Keep templates clean and organized
- Use template tags and filters appropriately
- Implement proper template security

## Forms
- Use Django forms for user input
- Implement proper form validation
- Use ModelForms when appropriate
- Handle form processing correctly
- Implement CSRF protection

## Database and Migrations
- Use Django's migration system
- Follow naming conventions for models and fields
- Implement proper database indexes
- Use database constraints when appropriate
- Follow Django's ORM best practices

## Security
- Implement CSRF protection
- Use Django's built-in security features
- Apply proper authentication and authorization
- Follow secure coding practices
- Protect against common web vulnerabilities

## Testing
- Write comprehensive unit and integration tests
- Use Django's testing framework
- Test models, views, and forms appropriately
- Use fixtures or factories for test data
- Follow testing best practices (AAA pattern)

## Settings Configuration
- Use environment-specific configurations
- Store sensitive information in environment variables
- Organize settings logically
- Use Django's settings inheritance
- Manage secrets appropriately

## Static Files
- Use Django's static files handling
- Implement proper static file organization
- Follow best practices for CSS and JavaScript
- Optimize static files for production
- Use CDN when appropriate

## Admin Interface
- Customize admin interface appropriately
- Implement proper admin security
- Use admin features effectively
- Follow admin best practices
- Extend admin functionality when needed

## Performance
- Use database optimization techniques
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use select_related and prefetch_related appropriately
- Optimize queries and avoid N+1 problems
- Profile and monitor application performance

## Authentication and Authorization
- Use Django's authentication system
- Implement custom user models when needed
- Apply proper permission systems
- Follow best practices for user management
- Implement secure password handling